.TH 9p-setattr 5 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
9p setattr \- change file status information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
size[4] Tsetattr tag[2] fid[4] valid[4] mode[4] uid[4] gid[4] size[8]
                 atime_sec[8] atime_nsec[8] mtime_sec[8] mtime_nsec[8]
size[4] Rsetattr tag[2]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
setattr sets file status information.
Only the attributes with appropriate bit set in the valid[4] mask are changed.
.TP
\fIvalid[4]\fR
A bitmask specifying which attributes are to be set (see below).
.TP
\fImode[4]\fR
File permission bits.
.br
Valid if P9_SETATTR_MODE (0x1) is set in the valid[4] mask.
.TP
\fIuid[4]\fR
File id of the file.
.br
Valid if P9_SETATTR_UID (0x2) is set in the valid[4] mask.
.TP
\fIgid[4]\fR
Group id of the file.
.br
Valid if P9_SETATTR_GID (0x4) is set in the valid[4] mask.
.TP
\fIsize[8]\fR
File size.
.br
Valid if P9_SETATTR_SIZE (0x8) is set in the valid[4] mask.
.TP
\fIatime_sec[8]\fR, \fIatime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last file access, seconds and nanoseconds.
Valid if P9_SETATTR_ATIME (0x10) and P9_SETATTR_ATIME_SET (0x80) are set
in the valid[4] mask.
If the former is set and the latter is clear, the atime is set to the server's
current time.
.TP
\fImtime_sec[8]\fR, \fImtime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last file modification, seconds and nanoseconds.
Valid if P9_SETATTR_MTIME (0x20) and P9_SETATTR_MTIME_SET (0x100) are set
in the valid[4] mask.
If the former is set and the latter is clear, the mtime is set to the server's
current time.
.SH ORIGIN
9P2000.L
.SH SEE ALSO
9p-intro(5)
